headline: Does MetLife Still Offer Value After Latest Fed Rate Decision and Strong Three Year Gains?
summary: If you find yourself weighing whether to hold onto, buy, or maybe even trim your position in MetLife, you are not alone. The stock finished at $81.62 most recently, which puts its short-term returns in a fairly tight range. Over the last week, MetLife dipped by just -0.5%, with a slightly positive 1.4% lift over the past month.
